lemma mem_orIntroL [Entailment.HasAxiomOrInst L] (hѕЖ : ѕЖ вИИ T.theory) : ѕЖ вЛО ѕИ вИИ T.theory := by
  apply T.imp_closed (ѕЖ := ѕЖ);
  . exact orIntroL;
  . assumption;
```

This is proving that if `ѕЖ` is in the theory `T`, then `ѕЖ вИ® ѕИ` is also in `T`. This is using the fact that `T` is `imp_closed`. The implication `ѕЖ вЖТ (ѕЖ вИ® ѕИ)` is true by `or.intro left`, and since `ѕЖ` is in `T`, then `ѕЖ вИ® ѕИ` is also in `T`.

```tactics
