```tactics
def construction (T : FTheory L) (hT : ѕЗ вЮЭ ќЊ вИЙ T.theory) : вДХ вЖТ Set (Formula вДХ)
  | 0 => { ќі | ѕЗ вЮЭ ќі вИИ T.theory }
  | i + 1 =>
    match (decode i) with
    | some ќі =>
      letI T' := construction T hT i
      if вИА ќУ : Finset (Formula _), вЖСќУ вКЖ T' вЖТ ќУ.conj вЛП ќі вЮЭ ќЊ вИЙ T.theory then insert ќі T'
      else T'
    | none => construction T hT i
```

This defines a recursive set `construction T hT i`. The base case `i = 0` is the set of all `ќі` such that `ѕЗ вЖТ ќі` is in `T`. The inductive step `i + 1` takes the previous set `T'` and adds `ќі` to it if `T'` does not contain `ќі` and `ќі` satisfies a certain property (related to `hT`).

```tactics
def construction_omega (T : FTheory L) (hT : ѕЗ вЮЭ ќЊ вИЙ T.theory) : Set (Formula вДХ) := вЛГ i, construction T hT i
```

This defines the set `construction_omega T hT` as the union of all `construction T hT i` for `i : вДХ`.

```tactics
lemma subset_construction_succ : construction T hT i вКЖ construction T hT (i + 1) := by
  dsimp [construction];
  split;
  . split <;> tauto;
  . tauto;
```

This lemma proves that each set `construction T hT i` is a subset of the next set `construction T hT (i + 1)`. This is true because `insert ќі T'` is a superset of `T'`.

```tactics
lemma subset_construction_add : construction T hT i вКЖ construction T hT (i + j) := by
  induction j with
  | zero => simp;
  | succ j ih =>
    trans construction T hT (i + j);
    . apply ih;
    . apply subset_construction_succ;
```

This proves that `construction T hT i` is a subset of `construction T hT (i + j)` for any `j`. This follows from the fact that `i + j = i + (j - 1) + 1` and we can use induction.

```tactics
lemma monotone_construction (hij : i вЙ§ j) : construction T hT i вКЖ construction T hT j := by
  obtain вЯ®k, rflвЯ© := le_iff_exists_add.mp hij;
  apply subset_construction_add;
```

This proves that the sets `construction T hT i` are monotone with respect to `i`. This follows from `i вЙ§ j вЖТ i + k = j` for some `k`.

```tactics
lemma mem_omega_of_mem (h : ѕЗ вЮЭ ќі вИИ T.theory) : ќі вИИ construction_omega T hT := by
  simp only [construction_omega, Set.mem_iUnion];
  use 0;
  simpa [construction];
```

This lemma states that if `ќі` is in `T` (specifically, `ѕЗ вЖТ ќі вИИ T`), then `ќі` is in `construction_omega T hT`. This is true because `ќі` is in `construction T hT 0`.

